1ï¸âƒ£ What is Stream?
Stream is a modern way to process Collections (List, Set, etc.) in Java using a pipeline like:
filter â†’ map â†’ sort â†’ collect

âœ… Stream way
List<Integer> even = numbers.stream()
        .filter(n -> n % 2 == 0)
        .toList();

âœ… Filter (condition)
List<Integer> nums = List.of(1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8,9);
List<Integer> greaterThan5 = nums.stream().filter(n -> n > 5).toList();

âœ… Map (transform)
List<String> names = List.of("anurag", "amit", "rahul");
List<String> upper = names.stream().map(String::toUpperCase).toList();

âœ… Distinct
List<Integer> nums = List.of(1,2,2,3,3,4,5);
List<Integer> unique = nums.stream().distinct().toList();

âœ… Sorted
List<Integer> nums = List.of(5,1,3,2,4);
List<Integer> sorted = nums.stream().sorted().toList();

4ï¸âƒ£ Reduce / Sum
âœ… Sum
List<Integer> nums = List.of(1,2,3,4,5);
int sum = nums.stream().mapToInt(i -> i).sum();

âœ… Reduce
int sum = nums.stream().reduce(0, Integer::sum);

5ï¸âƒ£ Object Example (Very Important)
POJO
class User {
    public int id;
    public String name;
    public int age;
}
Sample List
List<User> users = List.of(
    new User(1, "Anurag", 35),
    new User(2, "Amit", 28),
    new User(3, "Rahul", 40)
);

âœ… Get users whose age > 30
List<User> seniors = users.stream().filter(u -> u.age > 30).toList();

âœ… Get only names
List<String> names = users.stream().map(u -> u.name).toList();

âœ… Find user with id = 2
User user = users.stream().filter(u -> u.id == 2).findFirst().orElseThrow();

âœ… Check if any user age > 60
boolean anySenior = users.stream().anyMatch(u -> u.age > 60);

âœ… Average age
double avgAge = users.stream().mapToInt(u -> u.age).average().orElse(0);

6ï¸âƒ£ API Automation Real Example
JSON Response
[
  { "id": 1, "name": "Anurag", "age": 35 },
  { "id": 2, "name": "Amit", "age": 28 },
  { "id": 3, "name": "Rahul", "age": 40 }
]
POJO
class User {
    public int id;
    public String name;
    public int age;
}
Convert JSON â†’ List<User> (Jackson)
ObjectMapper mapper = new ObjectMapper();
List<User> users = mapper.readValue(response,new TypeReference<List<User>>() {});

Use Stream on API response
âœ… Get names of users age > 30
List<String> seniorNames = users.stream().filter(u -> u.age > 30).map(u -> u.name).toList();

âœ… Find user with id = 2
User user = users.stream().filter(u -> u.id == 2).findFirst().orElseThrow();

7ï¸âƒ£ Important Rules
âŒ Stream is not reusable
Stream<Integer> s = nums.stream();
s.forEach(System.out::println);
s.forEach(System.out::println); // âŒ ERROR

âœ… Stream is lazy
nums.stream().filter(n -> n > 5); // Nothing happens until terminal operation

8ï¸âƒ£ Parallel Stream
nums.parallelStream().forEach(System.out::println);

9ï¸âƒ£ Interview One-Liner
Java Streams provide a functional, declarative way to process collections using filter, map, and reduce operations.

